raw: * A *date field* is like a combo box with the date as popup. As button to
* open the calendar a calendar icon is shown at the right to the textfield.
* To be conform with all form widgets, the {@link qx.ui.form.IForm} interface
* is implemented.
* The following example creates a date field and sets the current
* date as selected.
* <pre class='javascript'>
* var dateField = new qx.ui.form.DateField();
* this.getRoot().add(dateField, {top: 20, left: 20});
* dateField.setValue(new Date());
*
* @childControl list {qx.ui.control.DateChooser} date chooser component
* @childControl popup {qx.ui.popup.Popup} popup which shows the list control
* @childControl textfield {qx.ui.form.TextField} text field for manual date entry
* @childControl button {qx.ui.form.Button} button that opens the list control

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
A date field is like a combo box with the date as popup. As button to open the calendar a calendar icon is shown at the right to the textfield. To be conform with all form widgets, the {@link qx.ui.form.IForm} interface is implemented. The following example creates a date field and sets the current date as selected. 

 var dateField = new qx.ui.form.DateField();
 this.getRoot().add(dateField, {top: 20, left: 20});
 dateField.setValue(new Date());

@childControl.name: @childControl
@childControl.body: popup {qx.ui.popup.Popup} popup which shows the list control

@childControl.name: @childControl
@childControl.body: textfield {qx.ui.form.TextField} text field for manual date entry
